      "content": "i see what you mean about the climate aspect. but what about people who argue that it's just a way to push certain people out of the city? like, if you're a worker who lives somewhere where there's no subway and you have to drive to work, isn't this policy basically saying they don't belong in the urban core anymore? it feels like there's a massive tension there between environmental goals and social equity.",
